From: chat-template-patches
Subject: [Q3.6-7] Strengthened <IMPORTANT> tool-call instructions block (opt-in)

Targets: templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja (state after Q3.6-1 + Q3.6-2 + Q3.6-3 + Q3.6-4 + Q3.6-5 + Q3.6-6 applied)

Status: OPT-IN. This patch is NOT applied to the shipped patched/35B-A3B.jinja.
It edits the in-prompt instruction text rather than fixing a render-level bug,
so its effect is not verifiable by a render-diff the way the active Q3.6-N
patches are. Apply it if you observe the documented tool-call formatting
failure modes; otherwise leave it out. (Same treatment as Gemma 4's G8 and the
guidance-only G6.)

Upstream Qwen3.6's <IMPORTANT> reminder has four bullets. This patch adds three
that target documented, reproducible Qwen-coder tool-call formatting failures:

- "Do NOT omit the opening <tool_call> tag" — QwenLM/Qwen3-Coder#475 (model
  emits <function=...> without the wrapping <tool_call>).
- "...MUST be at the very beginning of a new line, with NO leading spaces or
  indentation" — block/goose#6883 (indented tool calls miss the parser).
- "...output a separate, completely closed <tool_call></tool_call> block for
  EACH function. Do NOT nest <tool_call> blocks" — block/goose#6883 +
  parallel-call nesting reports.

The change is purely additive guidance to the model; it does not alter the
tool-call wire format for well-formed output. The existing four bullets are
retained (with terminal punctuation normalized for consistency).

Prior art: jscott3201's public Qwen3.6 fork gist
e4b155885cc68c038d6ac8909a3bd9fe (its patch "Q6", where the strengthened block
is gated behind a `verbose_tool_instructions` kwarg defaulting true).
Snapshotted at docs/sources/gists/jscott3201-e4b15588-qwen36-custom.jinja. This
repo ships it as a flat opt-in patch (apply = enable) rather than adding a
kwarg gate.

Stacks on Q3.6-1 + Q3.6-2 + Q3.6-3 + Q3.6-4 + Q3.6-5 + Q3.6-6. Diff is against
the Q3.6-6-applied state.

--- a/templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja
+++ b/templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja
@@ -83,7 +83,7 @@
         {{- tool | tojson }}
     {%- endfor %}
     {{- "\n</tools>" }}
-    {{- '\n\nIf you choose to call a function ONLY reply in the following format with NO suffix:\n\n<tool_call>\n<function=example_function_name>\n<parameter=example_parameter_1>\nvalue_1\n</parameter>\n<parameter=example_parameter_2>\nThis is the value for the second parameter\nthat can span\nmultiple lines\n</parameter>\n</function>\n</tool_call>\n\n<IMPORTANT>\nReminder:\n- Function calls MUST follow the specified format: an inner <function=...></function> block must be nested within <tool_call></tool_call> XML tags\n- Required parameters MUST be specified\n- You may provide optional reasoning for your function call in natural language BEFORE the function call, but NOT after\n- If there is no function call available, answer the question like normal with your current knowledge and do not tell the user about function calls\n</IMPORTANT>' }}
+    {{- '\n\nIf you choose to call a function ONLY reply in the following format with NO suffix:\n\n<tool_call>\n<function=example_function_name>\n<parameter=example_parameter_1>\nvalue_1\n</parameter>\n<parameter=example_parameter_2>\nThis is the value for the second parameter\nthat can span\nmultiple lines\n</parameter>\n</function>\n</tool_call>\n\n<IMPORTANT>\nReminder:\n- Function calls MUST follow the specified format: an inner <function=...></function> block must be nested within <tool_call></tool_call> XML tags.\n- Do NOT omit the opening <tool_call> tag. Every function call MUST be wrapped in a complete <tool_call>...</tool_call> block.\n- The <tool_call> and <function> tags MUST be at the very beginning of a new line, with NO leading spaces or indentation.\n- Required parameters MUST be specified.\n- To call multiple functions, output a separate, completely closed <tool_call></tool_call> block for EACH function. Do NOT nest <tool_call> blocks inside one another.\n- You may provide optional reasoning for your function call in natural language BEFORE the function call, but NOT after.\n- If there is no function call available, answer the question like normal with your current knowledge and do not tell the user about function calls\n</IMPORTANT>' }}
     {%- if merged_system %}
         {{- '\n\n' + merged_system }}
     {%- endif %}
